symbol that that tells compiler to perform some operators 
a+b  here a&b is operent and + sign is operator
binari operator :- +(add) , -(sub) , *(multi) , /(divide) , %(modulo)
unari operator:- ++ (increment operator) , -- (decrement operator)

increment opretor :- 1: pre increment ++a(change value then use value)
                     2: post increment a++(use value then change value)

dectrement opr :- 1: pre decrement ++a(change value then use value)
                 2: post decrement a++(use value then change value)

relational operator:- == (equal to)
                     != (not equal)
                     > (grater)
                     < (lessthen)
                     >=(graterthen and equal to)
                     <=(lessthen and equal to)


logical opretor:- 1- && (logical AND ) :- both statment should be true then only true
                  2- || (logical OR) :-  at least one should be true then its true
                  3 - ! (logical NOT) :- reverse the statment ,converts true value to false and false to true.

 binary number system base 2 
 0 - 000
 1 - 001
 2 - 010
 3 - 011
 4 - 100
 5 - 101
 6 - 110
 7 - 111


catale - base 8
hexa decimal - base 18


bitwise operators:-
1. & (binary AND) : to palay with bits 
2. | (binari OR) : same as logic with bits
3. ^ (binary XOR) : similar value then FALSE different value then TRUE
4. ~ (binary one's complement) : 1 convert to 0 and 0 converted to 1 (to convert positive to negative andnagative to positive)
5. << (binary Left shift) : to sift the whole bit in Left 
   for example : if bit is 010 <<(left shift) 1(by 1) then ans will be 100
6. >> (binary Right sift) : to sift the whole bit in right
   for example : if bit is 010 >>(right shift) 1(by 1) then ans will be 001

assignment operator
1. = : to store the value
2. += : a = a+b
3. -= : a = a-b
4. *= : a = a*b
5. /= : a = a/b
